      <!--BEGIN English Content-->
<div class="english"> All of your linked Bank of America and Merrill Lynch accounts appear on the Accounts screen. Tap an account to view transaction details for the past 90 days. To view previous details or to view accounts that only show balances, sign in to the Online Banking website.<sup>1</sup> <br>
         <br>
         <strong>Add or Change a Travel Notice</strong> <br>
         <ul>
            <li>Go to <strong>Help &amp; Support</strong> on the main menu</li>
            <li>Tap <strong>Add or Change a Travel Notice</strong></li>
            </ul>
               <div class="or"> Or </div>
            <ul>
            <li>Tap your checking or credit card account</li>
            <li>Tap the <strong>I Want To …</strong> tab at the bottom</li>
            <li>If you’re adding a new notice, there will be an <strong>Add a Travel Notice</strong> button</li>
            <li>If you have an existing notice, there will be an <strong>Add or Delete Travel Notice</strong> button</li>
            <li>Tap the button, and you can add or edit information for your trip:
               <ul>
               <li>Travel dates</li>
               <li>Destinations</li>
               <li>Contact preferences</li>
            </ul>
            </li>
            
            </ul>
               <div class="or"> Or </div>
            <ul>
            <li>On iPads, go to <strong>Help &amp; Support</strong></li>
            <li>Tap <strong>I Want To … Add or Change a Travel Notice</strong></li>
            <li>Or go to your checking or credit card account and tap the <strong>arrow</strong> icon next to Available Balance/Current Balance and add a notice from there</li>
         </ul>
         <br>
         <br>
         <strong>Schedule an Appointment</strong> <br>
         <br>
         You can sign in and some of your information will be pre-filled, or you can schedule an appointment without signing in. If you sign in, you can also change or cancel already scheduled appointments.
         <ul>
            <li>Go to <strong>Contact Us</strong> on the main menu</li>
            <li>Tap <strong>Schedule an Appointment</strong></li>
            </ul>
               <div class="or"> Or </div>
            <ul>
