</p></div><div class="ot-desc-cntr ot-hide" role="tabpanel" tabindex="0" id="ot-desc-id-CCBA"><div class="ot-grp-hdr1"><h4 class="ot-cat-header">Opt-Out Preference Signals</h4><div class="ot-tgl"><input type="checkbox" name="ot-group-id-CCBA" id="ot-group-id-CCBA" role="switch" class="category-switch-handler" data-optanongroupid="CCBA" checked="" aria-labelledby="ot-header-id-CCBA"> <label class="ot-switch" for="ot-group-id-CCBA"><span class="ot-switch-nob" aria-label="Opt-Out Preference Signals"></span> <span class="ot-label-txt">Opt-Out Preference Signals</span></label> </div><div class="ot-tgl-cntr"></div></div><p class="ot-grp-desc ot-category-desc">An “opt-out preference signal,” such as the Global Privacy Control, is a signal sent by your browser, device, or other platform that communicates your choice for sharing personal information. Bank of America honors any opt-out preference signal that meets legal requirements as a valid request to opt out of sharing personal information for cross-context behavioral advertising. &nbsp;
